# Package Structure

## Key Configuration Files

### `__package.json`
All packages use a `__package.json` template file as the source of truth. Detailed formatting, template params, and `unitConfig` rules are defined in [Package JSON Format](./json-format.mdc).

### Root `package.json`
The root `package.json` is generated from the root `__package.json` template during BAI prepare/init.

## Library Structure
### Library Packages

```
{package-name}/
├── _docs        # Will hold all the mds describing the package          
├── shared/                  # Shared types and interfaces        (unitConfig.type: "typescript-lib")
├   ├── LICENSE      
├   ├── /src/main
├   ├   └── {db-entity-name} (when have db entities)
├── frontend                 # Frontend modules and UI components (unitConfig.type: "typescript-lib")
├   ├── LICENSE      
├   ├── /src/main
├   ├   ├── components (where applicable)
├   ├   ├── utils (where applicable)
├   ├   ├── pages (where applicable, each will be exposed only by its route and will not be disclosed from the package)
├   ├   ├── modules (will hold all the modules and a single module-pack or contextual module-packs for the package)    
├   ├   └── index.ts (will contextually export package function, if the package is small, everything would be exported from the default export)
├   └── src/test (where applicable)
└── backend/src/main         # Backend modules and services       (unitConfig.type: "typescript-lib")
    ├── LICENSE      
    ├   ├── components (where applicable)
    ├   ├── utils (where applicable)
    ├   ├── pages (where applicable, each will be exposed only by its route and will not be disclosed from the package)
    ├   ├── modules (will hold all the modules and a single module-pack or contextual module-packs for the package)    
    ├   └── index.ts (will contextually export package function, if the package is small, everything would be exported from the default export)
    └── src/test (where applicable)
```

### Application Packages

```
app/
├── frontend/        # Frontend application (unitConfig.type: "firebase-hosting")
└── backend/         # Backend application (unitConfig.type: "firebase-function")
```

### All Package contains:
- `src/main/` with module exports
- `src/test/` where applicable
- `tsconfig.json` in auto generated into the source folders (main / test / etc) unless explicitly defined in the unit config

## Adding a New Library

1. Create directory structure
2. Add `src/main`, `src/test` or other where applicable
3. Create `__package.json` with appropriate `unitConfig.type`
4. Add relavent dependencies and devDependencies
5. Create minimal `src/main/index.ts`
6. Modules go

